data.text: Stock data for Reliance Industries Ltd in Oil & Gas Operations industry. Reliance Industries Limited is engaged in the activities of hydrocarbon exploration and production, petroleum refining and marketing, petrochemicals, advanced materials and composites, renewables (solar and hydrogen), retail and digital services. The Company’s segments include Oil to Chemicals (O2C), Oil and Gas, Retail and Digital Services. O2C segment includes refining, petrochemicals, fuel retailing, aviation fuel and bulk wholesale marketing. It includes a portfolio spanning transportation fuels, polymers, polyesters and elastomers. Oil and Gas segment is engaged in exploration and development, production of crude oil and natural gas. Retail segment includes consumer retail and a range of related services. Digital Services segment is engaged in the provision of a range of digital services. It also provides an oncology-focused healthcare platform, which focuses on technology-driven cancer care. Its subsidiaries include 7-India Convenience Retail Limited and Aaidea Solutions Limited.

recentNews.headline: Darshan Mehta, former managing director of Reliance Brands, passes away
recentNews.intro: Reliance Brands was established in 2007 under Mehta?s leadership. He led the creation of a portfolio of premium lifestyle brands for Reliance, bringing iconic labels to the Indian market.
recentNews.imagecaption: Mehta became a non-executive director on RBL?s board last November.

recentNews.headline: Jio Financial share price jumps over 3% as subsidiary NBFC introduces digital Loan Against Securities
recentNews.intro: Jio Financial share price has fallen 27% on a year-to-date (YTD) basis, while the stock is down more than 35% in six months. The shares of Reliance Industries-owned Jio Financial Services have declined 40% in the past one year.
recentNews.imagecaption: Jio Financial Services share price has declined 40% in the past one year.

recentNews.headline: Reliance share price crashes 7%, hits 52-week low amid stock market crash. Do you own?
recentNews.intro: Reliance Industries faced significant selling pressure on April 7, with shares dropping over 7% to a new 52-week low of  ?1,115.55 amid a global stock market selloff.
recentNews.imagecaption: Reliance share price crashes 7%, hits 52-week low amid stock market crash. Do you own?

recentNews.headline: Mcap of nine of top-10 most valued firms plunges by  ?2.9 lakh crore; TCS, RIL hit most
recentNews.intro: During the same week, the BSE Sensex dropped by 2,050.23 points (2.64%), and the NSE Nifty slid 614.8 points (2.61%).
recentNews.imagecaption: Mcap of nine of top-10 most valued firms plunges by  ?2.9 lakh crore; TCS, RIL hit most.

recentNews.headline: Proud father Mukesh Ambani says daughter Isha Ambani ?boss in office?, speaks about pushing women to forefront?
recentNews.intro: Mukesh Ambani shared his pride in his daughter Isha Ambani's leadership, calling her his 'boss' at Reliance. He also highlighted women leaders' roles in his companies and encouraged a positive mindset for entrepreneurs.
recentNews.imagecaption: File photo of RIL Chairman Mukesh Ambani speaking at an event in Guwahati, Assam. On April 5, he said daughter Isha Ambani is his boss in office.

recentNews.headline: Ram Navami 2025: Radhika Merchant ?feels proud? of Anant Ambani's completion of padyatra | Watch
recentNews.intro: Padyatra' of Anant Ambani, Director, Reliance Industries Limited completed today and arrived at Dwarkadhish Temple on the occasion of Ram Navami 2025
recentNews.imagecaption: Radhika Ambani speaks as Anant completes his padyatra on Ram Navami

recentNews.headline: Ram Navami 2025: Nita Ambani prays at Dwarkadhish Temple for Anant Ambani's padyatra, 'give him strength' | Watch
recentNews.intro: Anant Ambani, Director of Reliance Industries, completed a padyatra from Jamnagar to Dwarkadhish Temple for RamNavami, 2025. His mother, Nita Ambani, expressed pride in her son's journey and acknowledged the cultural impact of the participants.
recentNews.imagecaption: Gujarat: Nita Ambani speaks as Anant completes Padyatra (ANI Photo)

recentNews.headline: Tariffs set to impact India's petroleum product exports to the US
recentNews.intro: A bulk of the petroleum exports to the US from India comprises petrol or gasoline, which are currently taxed at 14%
recentNews.imagecaption: India became a key source of refined petroleum products from countries like the Netherlands and the US as India increased it intake of Russian oil due to deep discounts being offered. (Bloomberg)

recentNews.headline: Reliance partners with THIS European major for esports business in India. Details here
recentNews.intro: Reliance's Rise and BLAST Esports announced a collaboration to develop India's esports sector, creating a JV that combines expertise in media production and technology. This venture aims to enhance tournament management and marketing while tapping into the growing global interest in esports.
